      <description>&lt;figure id=&#34;attachment_2844&#34; aria-describedby=&#34;caption-attachment-2844&#34; style=&#34;width: 202px&#34; class=&#34;wp-caption alignright&#34;&gt;[&lt;img class=&#34;size-medium wp-image-2844 &#34; title=&#34;megamind&#34; src=&#34;http://juanthedesigner.files.wordpress.com/2011/06/megamind.jpg?w=202&amp;#038;resize=202%2C300&#34; alt=&#34;&#34; width=&#34;202&#34; height=&#34;300&#34; data-recalc-dims=&#34;1&#34; /&gt;][1]&lt;figcaption id=&#34;caption-attachment-2844&#34; class=&#34;wp-caption-text&#34;&gt;I love this poster art in the movie. Hilarious!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The family and I finally watched Megamind the other night.  I was really impressed. The story was creative and different, but I was mostly amazed with the facial expressions –  really sucked me into the story. Also, a few weeks ago, we watched How to Train Your Dragon for the first time.  That has to be my favorite Dreamworks film to date.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
